comments: Collins (ATL) sets the screen on Holiday (IND) and does not deliver contact.
Johnson (IND) jumps to the side of Young (ATL) and avoids making contact.
Leaf (IND) sets the screen on Young (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Collins (ATL) makes incidental contact with Johnson (IND) during the rebound.
Holiday (IND) makes marginal contact with Young (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Leaf (IND) sets the screen on Prince (ATL) and does not deliver contact.
Young (ATL) does not move his pivot foot after gathering his dribble.
RLS shows Holiday (IND) moves laterally into Young's (ATL) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR. The illegal contact causes Young to pin the ball against his body and pause his dribble.
Leaf (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Prince's (ATL) path and absorbs the initial contact.  He does not extend his arm into Prince when he disengages from the pick.
Johnson (IND) makes incidental contact with Young (ATL) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Huerter (ATL) makes contact with Reed's (IND) arm and affects his ability to gather the rebound.
Collins (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Sumner (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Reed's (IND) path and does not deliver contact.  The two players briefly engage and separate following the screen.
Johnson (IND) and Len (ATL) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Bembry (ATL) jumps into Sumner (IND) and makes contact with his body after the release of his jump shot that affects his ability to land safely.
